/agents/kiro.go` (only file modified)\\n\\n#### 1. Rewrite `RunPrompt` — pipe-based `--no-interactive` (no tmux)\\n\\nModel after Claude's `RunPrompt` (`e2e/agents/claude.go:113-170`). Uses `exec.CommandContext` with stdout/stderr pipes. Env vars (SIGV4) propagate naturally — no `env` wrapper needed.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (k *Kiro) RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error) {\\n    // ...config setup...\\n    args := []string{\\\"chat\\\", \\\"--no-interactive\\\", \\\"--trust-all-tools\\\", \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"entire\\\", prompt}\\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(cmdCtx, k.Binary(), args...)\\n    cmd.Dir = dir\\n    cmd.Stdout = &stdout\\n    cmd.Stderr = &stderr\\n    err := cmd.Run()\\n    // ...collect exit code and return Output...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Open questions to verify during implementation:**\\n- Exact flag: `--trust-all-tools` (from error message) — check `kiro-cli chat --help`\\n- Prompt passing: positional arg (user's test) vs `-p` flag\\n\\n#### 2. Rewrite `StartSession` — sequential `--no-interactive` commands\\n\\nSince interactive mode doesn't work with SIGV4, implement `Session` as a wrapper that runs a new `--no-interactive` command per `Send()`. This is the same approach the `setup-kiro-action` uses (all examples are single-shot `--no-interactive` calls).\\n\\n```go\\ntype KiroSession struct {\\n    kiro       *Kiro\\n    dir        string\\n    ctx        context.Context\\n    lastOutput string  // captured output from most recent Send\\n}\\n\\nfunc (k *Kiro) StartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error) {\\n    return &KiroSession{kiro: k, dir: dir, ctx: ctx}, nil\\n}\\n\\nfunc (s *KiroSession) Send(input string) error {\\n    out, err := s.kiro.RunPrompt(s.ctx, s.dir, input)\\n    s.lastOutput = out.Stdout + out.Stderr\\n    return err\\n}\\n\\nfunc (s *KiroSession) WaitFor(_ string, _ time.Duration) (string, error) {\\n    return s.lastOutput, nil  // command already completed in Send\\n}\\n\\nfunc (s *KiroSession) Capture() string { return s.lastOutput }\\nfunc (s *KiroSession) Close() error    { return nil }\\n```\\n\\n**Session interface** (`e2e/agents/agent.go:57-62`): `Send`, `WaitFor`, `Capture`, `Close`\\n\\n**Trade-off:** Each `Send` creates a separate kiro-cli process (separate agent-spawn/stop hooks). Multi-turn tests will exercise multiple single-turn sessions instead of one continuous session. This is acceptable because:\\n- Hooks still fire correctly per prompt\\n- File changes persist (same working directory)\\n- The alternative (interactive TUI) doesn't work with SIGV4 at all\\n- Single-turn is how `setup-kiro-action` uses kiro-cli in CI\\n\\n#### 3. Remove dead code\\n- Delete `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` helper (no longer needed without tmux)\\n- Delete incorrect comment about `--no-interactive` not firing hooks\\n- Remove the old `KiroSession` struct that wrapped `TmuxSession`\\n\\n#### 4. Adjust imports\\n- Keep: `context`, `encoding/json`, `errors`, `fmt`, `os`, `os/exec`, `strings`, `time`\\n- Remove if no longer used: any tmux-only imports\\n\\n## What stays the same\\n- `Bootstrap()` — validates SIGV4 env vars in CI (unchanged)\\n- Hook installation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/`) — unchanged\\n- CI workflows (`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`) — unchanged\\n- All other agent implementations — unchanged\\n\\n## Verification\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. CI E2E with `--agent kiro` should pass\\n\\n## Key files\\n- `e2e/agents/kiro.go` — only file modified\\n- `e2e/agents/claude.go:113-170` — reference for pipe-based `RunPrompt`\\n- `e2e/agents/agent.go:57-62` — `Session` interface\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/a6375286-82fb-48a9-90fd-f8e611e47d1b.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"a83ad831-c909-4739-94a8-4fb8fa3c129d\"